LAGOS â€“ The Lagos State Government has ordered all civil servants from Grade level 02-12 to stay at home for the next 14 days because of Coronavirus beginning from tomorrow. All top government officials have also been advised to engage in social isolation while those who just returned from foreign trips are to stay in self isolation for 14 days. Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu announced this while briefing the press on Sunday (today). The briefing is still ongoing as the time of going to press.